Reasoning: The paper deals with the application of the Shapley value to quantifying the contribution of a tuple to a query answer in the context of data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also extensively uses cooperative game theory, which suggests the category cs.GT (Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses algorithmic and complexity-theoretic results, which are relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also presents approximation algorithms, which are relevant to the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
